President Joe Biden has chosen Clare Martorana as the Federal Chief Information Officer (CIO) and administrator of the Office of Electronic Government at the Office of Management and Budget (OMB). Martorana has a background in improving digital experiences for both businesses and government. She previously served as the Chief Information Officer of the U.S. Office of Personnel Management, where she focused on delivering better digital-first services for the Federal workforce. Martorana also worked at the U.S. Department of Veterans Affairs, leading the agency's Digital Modernization effort. Before her government service, she held positions at Everyday Health and WebMD.